                              text is hardly legible because of faded ink.</desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- The Pss. are divided into groups of ten separated by a
                           chain of asterisks between two lines of alternating black and red dots.
                           
 - The scribe reduced the size of his handwriting to accommodate the
                           end of the line: e.g., <locus target="#13r">13r</locus>, 14v, 40r, 67r,
                           70r, 100v.
 - Part of the line is taken up: e.g., <locus target="#13v">13v</locus>, 49v, 88r, 90v, 98v.
 - Omissions
                           inserted interlineally, in the main hand: e.g., <locus target="#2r">2r</locus>, 57r, 64v, 77rv, 95v, 105ra; in a secondary hand: e.g.,
                              <locus target="#32v">32v</locus>, 43r.
 - Corrections written over
                           erased words and passages: e.g., <locus target="#12v">12v</locus>, 79r,
                           85r, 106va, 113rb.
 - Instructions concerning the use of some Pss.
                           written in a secondary hand: e.g., <locus target="#8v">8v</locus>, 11v,
                           31r, 57v.
 - Pen trial: <locus target="#114r">114r</locus>.
 -
                           Erased (supplication) notes: e.g., <locus target="#76v">76v</locus>,
                           77rv, 96v.
 - Short supplications for (ʾabuna) Gabra Masqal, in a
                           secondary hand: e.g., <locus target="#49r">49r</locus>, 55r.
 - Short
                           supplications in different hands: e.g, <locus target="#30r">30r</locus>
                           (name erased) and 96v.
 - Crude drawings (crosses and a human face):
                              <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 16v, 114v.
 - Crude notes in ink,
                           pen and pencil: <locus target="#1r">1r</locus> (hardly legible because of
                           faded ink), 55v, 56r, 73v, 99r, 113v, 114r.
 - Scribbles, in pencil:
                           e.g., <locus target="#1v">1v</locus>, 17r, 18v.</item>
                        <item xml:id="e2">
                           <desc type="findingAid">- Daily readings are indicated by the names of the
                              days of the week written in the margin, in pen and pencil: ዘሃሙስ, ዘሐሙስ:
                              fols. 49r, 55r ዘዓርብ: fols. 68r, 76r ዘቀደመ[sic]: <locus target="#78r">fol. 78r</locus>. - Red threads inserted in the right upper corner
                              of fols. 17r, 24r, 49r, 55r, 78r.</desc>
                        </item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
